[The illnesses in this cluster are, as yet, undefined. In the usual circumstances, hepatitis A in children tends to be mild, often totally without symptoms. In war torn Syria, however, with malnutrition and other stressors, increased morbidity and even mortality can occur. It is also possible that an alternative etiology is present, including non viral infections as well as toxins.

Maps of Syria can be seen at http://www.freeworldmaps.net/asia/syria/syria-political-map.jpg and https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=5420272,25782.
Al-Riqama village is located in Homs governorate, one of the 14 muhafazat (governorates or provinces) of Syria. Homs is situated in central Syria and is geographically the largest governorate of Syria. The governorate is divided into 6 administrative districts (mantiqah). Homs is the capital city of Homs district and governorate. - Mod.LL]
